title: 218 - Quadruple Sink
description:
Everyone wants to be great and be successful, but how many of you show up every day? On today’s podcast, ET talks about the importance of NOT checking out while on your journey to success. Life happens to everyone, but people who become GREAT keep pushing no matter what. While the greats keep pushing and elevating, ET talks to the people who are going AWOL and not showing up consistently. Not showing up in their business, in their marriage, and they wonder why they’re still average. Take notes from today’s episode on the process and importance of showing up consistently. 
 The Secret to Success Topics:
  [07:15] - Valentine’s Day
 [13:50] - Go To Bed
 [17:11] - AWOL
 [26:00] - Show Up
 [45:08] - Don’t Compromise
 [1:01:00] - No More Ideas
 [1:15:00] - Coach K Moment
  Listener Perks:
  Organifi is giving our listeners 20% off of their order just go to www.organifi.com/success. Their superfood green juice powder allows you to get your greens anytime anywhere while on the go.
 Join the 1% Club 
 For the Sermon mentioned in today’s Episode click  HERE

  Secrets 2 Success:
  A part of being successful is NOT going AWOL.
 You can’t go AWOL and expect to get the privileges that successful people have.
 You can not physically clock in and clock out.
 You can own what happens to you internally.
 The only way you shift your perspective is to think of others.
